title: 23 WAYS TO HAVE FUN AT HOME || APRIL FOOLS' DAY PRANKS
description:
Hilarious pranks for everyone at home

In this video, I show you how to make the best of April fools with these amazing prank ideas you should try. 
You can start your day by drawing a spider on the toilet paper in your bathroom. Anyone who’s terrified of spiders won’t even step in. 
You can also offer your friends some strawberries, but beforehand make sure you remove some of the fruit in the middle and fill it up with ginger or garlic.
You can also apply nail polish on a clean soap bar and put it in the bathroom. Nobody would be able to wash their hands with it. 
Another great idea is to dip Brussel sprouts in some chocolate sauce and serve them to your friend. 
You can also take an oreo cookie, remove the cream from the middle and replace it with toothpaste. 
Another fun idea is to open a bag of crisps and coat the top of it with Nutella. Then offer some crisps to your friends and watch their reaction. 

#StayAtHome

title: Fact check : क्या Tirupati Balaji ने 200 करोड़ और Ambani ने 1000 करोड़ Coronavirus के लिए दिए हैं?
description:
Read the complete story here: https://www.thelallantop.com/factcheck/fact-check-whatsapp-message-claims-hindu-celebrities-and-temples-donated-amounts-in-crores-for-the-fight-against-coronavirus-pandemic/

The Lallantop Fact check: Amid coronavirus outbreak in India, a message is being shared indiscriminately on social media claiming that Hindu temples and Hindu actors like Akshay Kumar, Varun Dhawan and industrialists like Mukesh Ambani have given a lot of donations in the time of coronavirus disaster. It is also being said in this message that nothing has been given from the places of worship and celebrations of other religions. 

In the investigation of 'The Lallantop', this claim turned out to be misleading. Watch the video by the Editor of 'The Lallantop' Saurabh Dwivedi to know the true facts behind the viral misleading claim related to donations during the COVID-19 pandemic.
